@startuml architecture-colocated

!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultFontName monospaced
skinparam nodesep 50
skinparam ranksep 40
skinparam padding 6

title Co-located — authorization as a JOIN (single database)

component "Application backend" as app #LightBlue

node "PostgreSQL" as pg {
    frame "app schema" as appschema #LightGreen {
        component "documents\norders, ..." as tables
    }
    frame "authz schema (engine)" as authz #Orange {
        component "check_access()\nlist_objects()\nwrite_tuple()" as fns
    }
}

app -down-> tables : one SQL statement:\nSELECT d.* FROM documents d\nJOIN authz.list_objects('store',\n  'user', :uid, 'can_read', 'document') a\n  ON a.object_id = d.id
tables -right-> fns : JOIN / RLS policy

app -down-> fns : business write + write_tuple()\nin ONE transaction\n(atomic grant with the data)

note bottom of pg
  No network hop: data filtering **and** the
  authorization decision run in the same query plan.
  Wildcard grants come back as a typed row
  (is_wildcard) instead of enumerating the store.
  App roles get EXECUTE on the function API only
  (SECURITY DEFINER) — never table grants.
end note

legend bottom left
  |= Color |= Component |
  | <#LightGreen> | Application schema — the app's own tables |
  | <#Orange> | authz schema — the pgauthz engine (functions + tuples) |
end legend

@enduml
